<br>
If you are stupid enough to do that for a few pixels, it's your choice. It does not entitle anyone else to do the same thing in game. It does suck for Chami for sure. But it's not a case of Chami vs Melissa, it's a case of Chami vs his own choice of sitting for weeks on and the game mechanics.<br>
<br>
That said even if I respect her choice, and I don't think she did anything wrong even if she was on the list, I would not do the same thing. Basically you have to either spend literally hundreds of RL hours in skyfire, or do it the normal way and have many people angry at you. What I would really do, is just not do the ragefire camp - NOTHING in the game could ever be worth so much trouble.<br>
<br>
The real problem here is the limited amount of content available to high level players. The ragefire thing is just one aspect of it. I did some tracking this morning and I think I can safely say that 95% of all significant mobs will be down by this evening. That's 36 hours after a patch, and only one evening for the north american players.<br>
