<br>
You have to remember, that my perspective on this is that of a person who had never heard of this list, until I happened to chance across this site, and found it to be over 80 people long. I don't like the list, never agreed to the list, and the list has effectively locked me out from EVER getting my epic. <br>
<br>
Saying that my statement equates to &quot;all behavior is perfectly acceptable and its fine to treat people however you want, as long as you don't break the law&quot; is a ridiculous jump in logic. Why should I respect the effort of others to monopolize a spawn, so that I can never get it?  The list is unfair, was not widely known at first, and is loaded down with people who happened to be the first to hear of it. <br>
<br>
As far as having respect for others, any person who has dealt with me in game knows that I am always respectful, and have never engaged in nasty, or unseemly behaviors. The point is, just because you SAY that you &quot;own&quot; a spawn, and have it reserved for the next two years, doesn't mean that you actually do. And doesn't it show disrespect for others efforts to tell a cleric who has everything but the heart that they must wait two years for the spawn, since they found out about the list late? There was a post on one of these boards from a lvl 60 cleric in just that situation.<br>
<br>
Personally, I plan to deal with the whole thing by not getting my epic, but I don't fault other people, who happened not to be insiders to the existence of this list, for wanting to get theirs. <p>Xaanru <br>
