<br>
Melissa, you did absolutely nothing wrong. Keep it and congrats to you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now... <br>
The list is in essence,  the minority trying to control the majority under the guise of morals.  <br>
If you don’t adhere to and support the list, you have no morals, you’re an ass, you’re a creep, you’re a moron, and then some.  You’re threatened with being “blacklisted” (haha), you’re called names, and you and the people associated with you are harrassed with tells, shouts, etc.<br>
<br>
Remember when RF spawned in Solb, clerics would actually have to put in some time and effort prior to even getting the CAMP for RF.<br>
<br>
A cleric that was interested in the SolB RF would have to find out who was currently camping RF and find out if someone was already next in line.   If not, the cleric would try to  work it out so that they could be next in line.  They would either hang out with the cleric currently camping RF and help kill FG’s, or asked to be notified (personally, thru their guild or thru friends).  <br>
<br>
If that person could not be found for whatever reason, the RF camp was then open to whoever got there first.  No one went overboard trying to “maintain”  a list of whoever was next in line.  The only person who ultimately had that responsibility was the person who actually wanted to camp RF next.<br>
<br>
If there were more than a couple people waiting to “be next”, you had one or two options.  Wait a week or two and check back – or continue to check back often.  I mean, you never knew, maybe someone didn’t show up after the last RF killing and the camp was open.<br>
<br>
People interested in RF, had no choice but to put forth some effort, and what good is that you ask?  Well, it definitely weeded out those that didn’t want to put out any effort.  It weeded out those that were too lazy, too preoccupied, or just didn’t care.<br>
<br>
Only those that were willing to put in the effort, got the RF camp &amp; hence their epic.<br>
<br>
It's a little different with the list.  The list encourages and supports those that otherwise wouldn’t stand a chance of getting RF, whether that be due to laziness, lack of support, or lack of interest.<br>
<br>
All you need to do is get your name on the list.<br>
<br>
You can get your name on the list and not even be RF ready.<br>
<br>
You can get your name on the list, and not have even started your epic yet.<br>
<br>
You can put your name on the list, and happily go about your way for months, maybe even years, knowing that when your time comes for RF, come hell or high water, someone will find you.   And if you can’t be found, someone with “higher morals” will defend your right to the camp anyway.  <br>
<br>
You can put your name on the list, go on vacation, out of town, log out of EQ for 6 months, and still rest easy knowing you haven’t lost your place in line – on ‘the list’<br>
<br>
Get rid of it<br>
