top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: can't seem to edit *sigh*</span><hr size=1> You know....<br>
<br>
I was going to post again, tossing more fuel on the fire, but as I thought through my arguments, I more and more see both sides of this.  There ARE a huge number of clerics that will do anything to get rage, KS, ignore the list, whatever... those people are not going away no matter what.  <br>
<br>
But in all fairness, there are just as many anti-list people that just feel the list is truly unfair because of how it evolved and how some people knew about it before others.  <br>
<br>
I do see both sides of this.<br>
<br>
That said, I still can't see jumping in on someone that has waited 5 days when I have not.<br>
<br>
So?  What to do.....<br>
<br>
If most of the server really want this to be fair and organized (do we?), maybe we should restart... Kill the list.... Get everyone on board with a brand new system.<br>
<br>
1) Create a database of clerics (over some level) that want the camp.<br>
<br>
2) New people get added whenever they want.<br>
<br>
3) Pick a cleric at random and that cleric gets first spawn.<br>
<br>
4) Pick a backup cleric at random, who gets next spawn.<br>
<br>
5) Every time rage is had, pick a new backup cleric at random.<br>
<br>
This could address the &quot;unfair&quot; arguments against the list. It would obviously suck for those atop the current list, but being those people are &quot;community minded&quot;, I'd wager they would agree if it would restore order. <br>
<br>
However, if many on the server want a FFA, then no list of any sort will ever work.  And it needs to be a community decision, not a minority based solution (which some claim the current list to be).<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd prefer either a completely role playing based situation, which would result in the same thing we have today, but at least would have some color and character (as opposed to RL name calling), or a completely OOC: list that everyone can agree to to solve this problem. <p><b><i><font face="Garamond"><font color="#993366"><font size=+2>
