<br>
It is true that generally speaking, if you are camping a spawn and go LD then come back 20 minutes later to find the camp taken, you have probably lost the camp.  But we all know Ragefire is a special sort of camp, due to the extreme length of time between spawns.  Thus if someone has been camping Rage for 5 days straight and goes LD for 20 mins, courtesy and respect for that person’s time, common decency! DEMAND that you allow sufficient time for them to log back in (reboot if necessary, it happens..ah technology...) <br>
<br>
I have heard the arguments about “no one in their right mind should be camping RF for days (weeks)”, but it’s a fact that it WILL happen, the cleric epic is a highly valued and useful item to all guilds, and if camping in the zone will give them the edge over someone else, they will do it.<br>
<br>
Given that this is so, the List was an attempt to bring some order where there was chaos, and try to cooperate in order to reduce the stress &amp; frustration factors (oh boy is THAT not working.)   It was poorly implemented, and is in need of a huge overhaul, but I won’t hijack this thread into another debate about what should be done to fix it.<br>
<br>
I don’t know Melissa, and I don’t think she is an ‘evil’ person for doing what she did, Ragefire brings out the worst in people.  Personally I would never trust her after this.  And many others won't, also.  <br>
<br>
